<h1>Final Remarks:</h1>
<p>There's a lot more to see and do (and taste) on Jeju Island besides what I covered. The must-see attractions are, according to the tourism websites, Hallasan National Park, Seongsan Ilchulbong, and the waterfalls. And even though this was my 4th time visiting Jeju, I always discover new things and places. So I recommend renting a car and exploring.</p>
<p>Jeju is a wonderful little island, full of options for every type of traveler. Beautiful beaches, great food, Korean street markets, plenty of mountains and hiking, a wide variety of hotels, pensions, and guest houses, and great urban and countryside balance.</p>
